ques call for breaking projects into phases and short-term goals, managing assignments collectively, and tracking progress openly. Agile Faculty is a comprehensive roadmap for scholars who want to incorporate Agile practices into all aspects of their academic careers, be it research, service, or teaching. Rebecca Pope-Ruark covers the basic principles of Scrum, one of the most widely used models, and then through individual chapters shows how to apply that framework to everything from individual research to running faculty committees to overseeing student class work. Practical and forward-thinking, Agile Faculty will help readers not only manage their time and projects but also foster productivity, balance, and personal and professional growth.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aAgile software development. 0aCollege teaching. 0aProject management. 0aScrum (Computer software development) 0aScrum (Computer software development). 0aUniversities and collegesxFaculty. 0aUniversities and colleges-Faculty. 7aEDUCATION / General.2bisacsh  aAgile.  aScrum.  afaculty development.  afaculty.  aproductivity.  aresearch.  aservice.  astrategies.  ateaching.  avitality.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z97831107119360 cprintz978022646301840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226463292423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226463292/original  a978-3-11-071193-6  University of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aGBV-deGruyter-alles